# Morphic — Project Constitution

Morphic is a Home Assistant **first-party custom-card collection** implementing
**Material 3 Expressive**, designed to be edited/extended with **Card-Mod**. The name
reflects M3 Expressive's signature shape-morphing.

## Architecture (cards-only, on top of an existing theme)
- We do **NOT** build a theme. Morphic rides on **Nerwyn/material-you-theme** + its
  companion **material-you-utilities** as the base color/token engine.
- Never hardcode `--md-sys-color-*`. The base palette is **user-defined** by the theme;
  read it at runtime.
- Every card styles itself from M3 tokens and **falls back gracefully** to native HA CSS
  vars (`--primary-color`, `--card-background-color`, ...) when off-theme.

## Token-only styling + Card-Mod contract
- Style **only** from tokens: public `--morphic-*` tokens and `--md-sys-color-*`.
- Card-Mod users override **public `--morphic-*` tokens only** — never internal selectors,
  shadow-DOM classes, or element structure. Treat the token surface as the public API
  (see `docs/token-contract.md`). Do not rename/remove public tokens without a doc update.

## Hard requirements
- **Sections-first** layout: every card implements `getGridOptions()` and is fully
  responsive via container queries / ResizeObserver — **no fixed pixel widths**.
- **Mobile-first**: one-handed reach, min 48dp touch targets, bottom nav, pop-ups over
  page jumps.
- Reuse **Bubble Card** (pop-ups) and **navbar-card** (bottom nav). Do not reimplement them.
- Design/document against the **Expressive** scheme; per-card accents come from the
  accent engine, never fixed hex.

## Core features (baked into shared base — inherit, don't re-add per card)
1. Theme-derived per-card **accent engine** (HCT seeds + `Blend.harmonize()`, deterministic
   hash selection, `color:` > `color_key:` > title > entity_id precedence).
2. Subtle **accent → primary gradient** fill (token-controlled intensity/angle).
3. Android-style **circle ↔ squircle icon-morph** for OFF/ON.
4. **Sections-first** responsive layout via `getGridOptions()`.
5. Polished **ha-form GUI editor** with live preview (never a raw YAML blob).
6. **SSH/SFTP** dev/deploy tooling.

## Deploy workflow
- Secrets live in a **gitignored `.env.deploy`** (template: `.env.deploy.example`):
  SSH host/port/user and remote path (e.g. `/config/www/morphic`). Auth is SSH-agent only.
- `npm run build` → Rollup prod build to `/dist`.
- `npm run deploy` → build, then SFTP `/dist` to remote.
- `npm run dev` → Rollup watch; auto-SFTP the rebuilt bundle on each success.
- Cross-platform (Windows/PowerShell friendly). **Never use rsync. Never commit secrets.**

## Not now
- **No HACS** yet. Do not add `hacs.json`/`info.md` or HACS validation to CI.
